                    "value": "<p>people will gratify a fancy and pay more in a<lb/> small way, than\n                                        subscribing to an entire work<lb/> such is the mean spirit\n                                        of this place, though<lb/> I do fortunately meet in my\n                                                  <add>?</add> with a<lb/> few expressions. My\n                                        literary friend would<lb/> rather feast on a good\n                                        substantial work<lb/> than all the dainties of the universe.\n                                        In<lb/> fact were it not for his librarying<lb/> mind (to\n                                        use your own adage) would long<lb/> since have gone to vast\n                                        so much am I indebt-<lb/>ed to my friend <persName>Mr Heyman\n                                                  Cohen Del<add>?</add></persName>;<lb/> a young\n                                        gentleman of good parts; clear mind<lb/> and would by little\n                                        practice be a fine lec-<lb/>turer; <add>?</add> for the\n                                        world he is only the merchant.<lb/> I should like to hear\n                                        some publications of<lb/> your honorable successor\n                                                  <persName>Mr. Morais.</persName> How<lb/> strange\n                                        it will appear to me should I reform,<lb/> to see another\n                                        occupying your place. <persName>Louisa</persName><lb/> seems\n                                        to regret much the state of affairs<lb/> when she last\n                                        wrote. <persName>Mrs H</persName> has not said<lb/> anything\n                                        on the subject but that was owing<lb/> to the melancholy\n                                        state of my feelings. I regret<lb/> exceedingly you did not\n                                        know the date of</p>"
